        Computes the final answer as a set of Voronoi regions. Each region is represented by a Geometry. The associated site for each Voronoi region is stored as user data inside the geometry. The polygon that represents each region is clipped to the given rectangle (MBR) to ensure the possibility of representing infinite open regions. The answer is split into final and non-final regions based on the given MBR.
